            <creation>This story, with the short title "Gabra Maryam and the Bound Prisoners," is recent: the earliest PEMM manuscript* in which this story appears is from around<date>1875</date>.Originally composed in <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName></creation>
            <abstract>
                <p>Gabra Maryam prayed to Mary, who appeared and took him to her sanctuary in Aksum. When they arrived, they found all the people there had been bound. Mary commanded their release, and they were instantly freed from their restraints. Having witnessed this miracle, Gabra Maryam returned to his monastery in amazement.</p>
